General.Name: iShares Short-Term California Muni Active ETF
General.Description: BlackRock ETF Trust II - iShares Short-Term California Muni Active ETF is an exchange traded fund launched by BlackRock, Inc. The fund is managed by BlackRock Fund Advisors. It invests in fixed income markets of the United States. The fund invests directly and through other funds in U.S. dollar-denominated investment-grade tax-exempt, short-term fixed- and floating-rate municipal securities issued by California with remaining maturities of five years or less that are rated BBB- or higher by S&P and/or Fitch or Baa3 or higher by Moody's. The fund seeks to benchmark the performance of its portfolio against the Bloomberg CA IG only 0-2yr Index. BlackRock ETF Trust II - iShares Short-Term California Muni Active ETF was formed on July 11, 2023 and is domiciled in the United States.
